@sen431   Some authors use the term "variation, in a technical sense, as implying a modification directly due to the physical conditions of life, and "variations, in this sense are supposed not to be inherited, but who can say that the dwarfed condition of shells in the brackish waters of the Baltic, or dwarfed plants on Alpine summits, or the thicker fur of an animal from far northwards, would not in some cases be inherited for at least a few generations?

