@sen560   Alphonse de Candolle and others have shown that plants which have very wide ranges generally present varieties, and this might have been expected, as they are exposed to diverse physical conditions, and as they come into competition, [which, as we shall hereafter see, is a far more important circumstance], with different sets of organic beings.

