 :: under domestication, other hand, become extinct, under nature, natural selection, any advantage, conditions of life ::

@sen810   But the variability, which we almost universally meet with in our domestic productions is not directly produced, as Hooker and Asa Gray have well remarked, by man, he can neither originate varieties nor prevent their occurrence, he can only preserve and accumulate such as do occur.

