              " (extract-fr) part 30 of Darwin about: other hand, has remarked, natural selection, this condition, effects of disuse

@sen1375   From the facts alluded to in the first chapter, I think there can be no doubt that use in our domestic animals has strengthened and enlarged certain parts, and disuse diminished them, and that such modifications are inherited.

              " (extract-fr) part 30 of Darwin about: other hand, has remarked, natural selection, this condition, effects of disuse

