@sen1383   Kirby has remarked, [and I have observed the same fact], that the anterior tarsi, or feet, of many male dung-feeding beetles are often broken off, he examined seventeen specimens in his own collection, and not one had even a relic left.

              " (extract-fr) part 30 of Darwin about: other hand, has remarked, natural selection, this condition, effects of disuse

