@sen1392   Wollaston, lie much concealed, until the wind lulls and the sun shines, that the proportion of wingless beetles is larger on the exposed Desertas than in Madeira itself, and especially the extraordinary fact, so strongly insisted on by Mr.

              " (extract-fr) part 30 of Darwin about: other hand, has remarked, natural selection, this condition, effects of disuse

