@sen1556   To explain by a simple example what is meant, if in a large genus of plants some species had blue flowers and some had red, the colour would be only a specific character, and no one would be surprised at one of the blue species varying into red, or conversely, but if all the species had blue flowers, the colour would become a generic character, and its variation would be a more unusual circumstance.

