@sen1802   Petrels are the most aerial and oceanic of birds, but, in the quiet sounds of Tierra del Fuego, the Puffinuria berardi, in its general habits, in its astonishing power of diving, in its manner of swimming and of flying when made to take flight, would be mistaken by any one for an auk or a grebe, nevertheless, it is essentially a petrel, but with many parts of its organisation profoundly modified in relation to its new habits of life, whereas the woodpecker of La Plata has had its structure only slightly modified.

              " (extract-fr) part 40 of Darwin about: other hand, become extinct, perfect characters

