              " (extract-fr) part 40 of Darwin about: other hand, become extinct, perfect characters

@sen1836   It has been objected that in order to modify the eye and still preserve it as a perfect instrument, many changes would have to be effected simultaneously, which, it is assumed, could not be done through natural selection, but as I have attempted to show in my work on the variation of domestic animals, it is not necessary to suppose that the modifications were all simultaneous, if they were extremely slight and gradual.

              " (extract-fr) part 40 of Darwin about: other hand, become extinct, perfect characters

