              " (extract-fr) part 47 of Darwin about: other plants, same plant, natural selection, closed flowers, through natural selection, some other plants

@sen2145   These two kinds of flowers sometimes differ wonderfully in structure, yet may be seen to graduate into each other on the same plant.

              " (extract-fr) part 47 of Darwin about: other plants, same plant, natural selection, closed flowers, through natural selection, some other plants

@sen2147   The closed and imperfect flowers are, however, manifestly of high importance, as they yield with the utmost safety a large stock of seed, with the expenditure of wonderfully little pollen.

              " (extract-fr) part 47 of Darwin about: other plants, same plant, natural selection, closed flowers, through natural selection, some other plants

@sen2150   In Ononis columnae five of the alternate stamens are rudimentary, and in some species of Viola three stamens are in this state, two retaining their proper function, but being of very small size.

              " (extract-fr) part 47 of Darwin about: other plants, same plant, natural selection, closed flowers, through natural selection, some other plants

@sen2153   de Jussieu, are still further modified, for the five stamens which stand opposite to the sepals are all aborted, a sixth stamen standing opposite to a petal being alone developed, and this stamen is not present in the ordinary flowers of this species, the style is aborted, and the ovaria are reduced from three to two.

              " (extract-fr) part 47 of Darwin about: other plants, same plant, natural selection, closed flowers, through natural selection, some other plants

