              " (extract-fr) part 48 of Darwin about: same manner

@sen2172   Aug. St. Hilaire gives the following cases, the genus Zanthoxylon belongs to a division of the Rutaceae with a single ovary, but in some species flowers may be found on the same plant, and even in the same panicle, with either one or two ovaries.

