              " (extract-fr) part 49 of Darwin about: than others

@sen2230   Mr. Mivart then asks, [and this is his second objection], if natural selection be so potent, and if high browsing be so great an advantage, why has not any other hoofed quadruped acquired a long neck and lofty stature, besides the giraffe, and, in a lesser degree, the camel, guanaco and macrauchenia?

              " (extract-fr) part 49 of Darwin about: than others

