              " (extract-fr) part 84 of Darwin about: south america, each other, existing groups, living species, living forms, existing genera, between existing genera

@sen3799   New species are formed by having some advantage over older forms, and the forms, which are already dominant, or have some advantage over the other forms in their own country, give birth to the greatest number of new varieties or incipient species.

