@sen3864   All that we have a right to expect is, that those groups which have, within known geological periods, undergone much modification, should in the older formations make some slight approach to each other, so that the older members should differ less from each other in some of their characters than do the existing members of the same groups, and this by the concurrent evidence of our best palaeontologists is frequently the case.

              " (extract-fr) part 85 of Darwin about: geological record, present day, each other, successive formations, living forms, conditions of life, right to expect, lengths of time

