@sen3991   No doubt small areas can be pointed out in the Old World hotter than any in the New World, but these are not inhabited by a fauna different from that of the surrounding districts, for it is rare to find a group of organisms confined to a small area, of which the conditions are peculiar in only a slight degree.

              " (extract-fr) part 88 of Darwin about: physical conditions, modified descendants, south america, other hand, natural selection, closely allied, same latitude

