@sen4099   The majority sank quickly, but some which, whilst green, floated for a very short time, when dried floated much longer, for instance, ripe hazel-nuts sank immediately, but when dried they floated for ninety days, and afterwards when planted germinated, an asparagus plant with ripe berries floated for twenty-three days, when dried it floated for eighty-five days, and the seeds afterwards germinated, the ripe seeds of Helosciadium sank in two days, when dried they floated for above ninety days, and afterwards germinated.

