@sen4851   Why should one crustacean, which has an extremely complex mouth formed of many parts, consequently always have fewer legs, or conversely, those with many legs have simpler mouths?

              " (extract-fr) part 107 of Darwin about: has remarked, other animals, certain extent, natural history, natural selection, same individual, metamorphosed leaves, serial homologies, such parts, many other animals

@sen4853   On the theory of natural selection, we can, to a certain extent, answer these questions.

