@sen4880   Such changes, however, reach their acme in the so-called alternate generations of some of the lower animals.

              " (extract-fr) part 108 of Darwin about: each other, growth alike, stages of development, later in life

@sen4881   It is, for instance, an astonishing fact that a delicate branching coralline, studded with polypi, and attached to a submarine rock, should produce, first by budding and then by transverse division, a host of huge floating jelly-fishes, and that these should produce eggs, from which are hatched swimming animalcules, which attach themselves to rocks and become developed into branching corallines, and so on in an endless cycle.

              " (extract-fr) part 108 of Darwin about: each other, growth alike, stages of development, later in life

@sen4882   The belief in the essential identity of the process of alternate generation and of ordinary metamorphosis has been greatly strengthened by Wagner's discovery of the larva or maggot of a fly, namely the Cecidomyia, producing asexually other larvae, and these others, which finally are developed into mature males and females, propagating their kind in the ordinary manner by eggs.

              " (extract-fr) part 108 of Darwin about: each other, growth alike, stages of development, later in life

